cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of neuroscience studies in object recognition and analyzes semantic-part characteristics of object category representations. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents an approach for analyzing object category representations. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of category-epitome, a spatial representation for objects. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves semantic-part annotations and word cloud visualizations. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely sub-category as the paper only briefly mentions the use of neuroscience studies in object recognition.
